5. Write a Program to create a list of all numbers in a range which are perfect 
squares and the sum of the digits of the number is less than 10. 
Sample Input & Output: 
Enter lower range: 1 
Enter upper range: 40 
[1, 4, 9, 16, 25, 36]

CODE: 
public class PerfectSquares {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Input range (change these to test)
        int lower = 1;
        int upper = 40;

        System.out.print("[");
        boolean first = true; // to handle commas

        for (int i = lower; i <= upper; i++) {
            int sqrt = (int) Math.sqrt(i);
            if (sqrt * sqrt == i) { // check perfect square
                if (sumOfDigits(i) < 10) {
                    if (!first) {
                        System.out.print(", ");
                    }
                    System.out.print(i);
                    first = false;
                }
            }
        }
        System.out.println("]");
    }

    // Helper method to calculate sum of digits
    public static int sumOfDigits(int num) {
        int sum = 0;
        while (num > 0) {
            sum += num % 10;
            num /= 10;
        }
        return sum;
    }
}
OUTPUT: 
[1, 4, 9, 16, 25, 36]
